      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:21:2",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُهُ يَقُولُ رَأْيُ الْمُؤْمِنِ وَ رُؤْيَاهُ فِي آخِرِ الزَّمَانِ عَلَى سَبْعِينَ جُزْءاً مِنْ أَجْزَاءِ النُّبُوَّةِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473164\">H 14506</a> – Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hashaam Bin Saalim, who has narrated:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-i\">‘I</span> heard Abu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The opinion and the dream of a ‘Momin’ (Believer), and what he sees in the later portion of the time is a seventieth part of the parts of the Prophet-hood’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "58. Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hashaam Bin Saalim, who has narrated: ‘I heard Abu Abdullah (a.s.) saying: ‘The opinion and the dream of a ‘Momin’ (Believer), and what he sees in the later portion of the time is a seventieth part of the parts of the Prophet-hood’."
        ]
